# Style Guide

_Template. Fill in per project. Doctor warns when absent and `.tsx` files exist._

## Why this file exists

Component-level rules: how to compose primitives, what patterns we use, what patterns we avoid. Read `docs/brand-guide.md` first for the visual identity; this file is the implementation contract on top of it.

Every component PR should follow these rules. The kit's Evaluator subagent grades against them during sprint review.

---

## Component anatomy

Every component file structure:

```tsx
/**
 * <ComponentName> -- one-sentence description of what it renders.
 *
 * Why it exists: what problem it solves that couldn't be done with
 * the primitive it wraps. If you can't answer this in one sentence,
 * the component shouldn't exist.
 */
import { /* primitives from design-system only */ } from '@/components/ui';

interface <ComponentName>Props {
  /* minimal props interface */
}

export function <ComponentName>(props: <ComponentName>Props) {
  /* no local state unless genuinely necessary */
  /* no data fetching -- components are pure renderers */
  return <div>...</div>;
}
```

Rules:

- File name matches component name: `Foo.tsx` exports `function Foo`.
- One component per file (primitives + composition) — exception: tightly coupled sub-components private to a file.
- Every component has a one-sentence "why it exists" docstring. Delete the component if you can't write it.
- Every component has a `.stories.tsx` sibling (enforced by kit — doctor counts ratio).

---

## Props discipline

- **Never** accept `className` as a user-facing knob unless you've documented exactly which classes are allowed.
- **Never** accept `style` as a prop. Use tokens from `docs/brand-guide.md`.
- **Prefer variants to conditionals.** `variant="primary"` not `isPrimary={true}`.
- **Enum variants over booleans.** Three booleans is one enum with four values and one invariant violation.

