## CSS Variable Naming Conventions

All design tokens are declared as CSS custom properties.

### Naming pattern

```
--{category}-{name}
```

Categories: `--color-*`, `--space-*`, `--radius-*`, `--shadow-*`, `--font-*`, `--motion-*`, `--ease-*`, `--z-*`.

### Theme-adaptive variables

```css
:root {
  --bg: var(--color-bg-dark);
  --text: var(--color-text-dark);
}

[data-theme="light"] {
  --bg: var(--color-bg-light);
  --text: var(--color-text-light);
}
```

---

## Using Brand Tokens (Correct vs Incorrect)

### Correct

```tsx
<div className="bg-[var(--bg)] text-[var(--text)] rounded-[var(--radius-md)]">
  <button className="bg-[var(--accent)] text-white">Action</button>
</div>
```

### Incorrect

```tsx
// WRONG: hardcoded values
<div className="bg-[#18181b] text-[#fafafa]">
  <button className="bg-[#6366f1]">Action</button>
</div>
```

```tsx
// WRONG: no dark/light mode support
<div style={{ background: '#fff', color: '#000' }}>...</div>
```

```tsx
// WRONG: arbitrary breakpoints
@media (min-width: 900px) { ... }
```

