## Styling

- Tokens from `docs/brand-guide.md`, not arbitrary values.
- `className` composition via `clsx` or `cn()` helper. Never string concatenation.
- No CSS-in-JS at runtime. Tailwind utility classes or CSS Modules only.
- Dark mode via `dark:` variants, not `data-theme` attributes.

---

## Accessibility

- Every interactive element has a visible focus ring (`focus-visible:ring-2`).
- Every icon-only button has `aria-label`.
- Every form field has a `<label>` or `aria-labelledby`.
- Keyboard navigation works before mouse: tab, enter, escape, arrow keys.
- Colour is never the only channel for meaning. Pair with icon or text.
- Target minimum 4.5:1 contrast (AA) for body text, 3:1 for large text.

Doctor's UI Coverage check verifies accessibility tests exist via `vitest-axe` or `@axe-core/playwright`.

---

## Performance

- Lazy load routes: `import { foo } from ...` at the top is fine for components that are always rendered. For heavy features, use dynamic `import()` + `Suspense`.
- Image optimisation: `next/image` always. No raw `<img>` in production code.
- No inline event handler closures in list renders — memoise or lift.

---

## Don't

- Don't `useState` for data you can derive.
- Don't `useEffect` to sync state to props — derive directly.
- Don't guard JSX with `&&` on numbers (`{count && ...}` renders "0").
- Don't nest ternaries more than one level deep.
- Don't use `React.FC` — use plain function components with typed props.

---

## Testing

Each component requires, per kit UI-coverage rules:

- `<name>.stories.tsx` — Storybook (enforced)
- Visual-regression snapshot on mobile-light, mobile-dark, desktop-light, desktop-dark
- A11y test (vitest-axe or playwright + @axe-core)

Pages additionally require e2e-video.

